---
description: Enforce Next.js feature-driven architecture + imports
alwaysApply: true
---

# Project architecture (permanent)

- **Folders are permanent**: do not reorganize `src/app`, `src/features`, `src/shared`, `src/core`.
- **Routing**: only App Router pages/layouts in `src/app/**`.
- **Domain code**: put feature code in `src/features/<feature>/**` (components/hooks/services/types/utils).
- **Reusable code**: put cross-feature code in `src/shared/**` (components/hooks/lib/constants/types).
- **Core infra**: put providers/store/api/config/middleware in `src/core/**`.

# Imports + exports

- **Absolute imports only**: use `@/…` (no `../../..` except inside the same folder when appropriate).
- **Barrel exports required**: prefer `index.ts` re-exports for clean imports.
- **Import from barrels** when available (e.g. `@/shared/components`, `@/core/api`).

# Components

- Keep UI components **pure and reusable**; move business logic into hooks/services.
- Avoid deeply nested JSX; split into smaller components.
